This paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm to color any 3-colorable <italic>n</italic>-node graph with <italic>O</italic>(<italic>n</italic><supscrpt>2/5</supscrpt> log<supscrpt>8/5</supscrpt> <italic>n</italic>) colors, improving the best previously known bound of <italic>O</italic>(√<italic>n</italic>/√log<italic>n</italic>) colors. By reducing the number of colors needed to color a 3-colorable graph, the algorithm also improves the bound for <italic>k</italic>-coloring for fixed <italic>k</italic> ≥ 3 from the previous <italic>O</italic>((<italic>n</italic>/log <italic>n</italic>)<supscrpt>1-1/(<italic>k</italic>-1)</supscrpt>) colors to <italic>O</italic>(<italic>n</italic><supscrpt>1-1/(<italic>k</italic>-4/3)</supscrpt> log<supscrpt>8/5</supscrpt> <italic>n</italic>) colors. An extension of the algorithm further improves the bounds. Precise values appear in a table at the end of this paper.